                            <comment id="13044329" author="srowen" created="Sat, 4 Jun 2011 17:38:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I can commit this; I imagine you certainly know what you&apos;re doing but are there any thread-safety concerns here? looks like the reused object is thread-local... haven&apos;t thought through the implications though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13044336" author="rcmuir" created="Sat, 4 Jun 2011 18:13:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;right, Analyzer is thread-safe: the reused streams are stored in a threadlocal: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/lucene/dev/trunk/lucene/src/java/org/apache/lucene/analysis/Analyzer.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/lucene/dev/trunk/lucene/src/java/org/apache/lucene/analysis/Analyzer.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when you call reusableTokenStream(), it grabs the per-thread saved one and calls reset() instead of creating a new one... creating a new one (all the tokenstreams and attributes) is very heavy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13044390" author="hudson" created="Sat, 4 Jun 2011 21:51:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #860 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/860/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/860/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-706&quot; title=&quot;reuse lucene tokenstreams&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-706&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-706&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; use reusable TokenStream in Lucene for performance&lt;/p&gt;

